Package de.hshl.obj.meta

Some classes meant to simplify the usage of the Java language in this project.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Reflective
    A collection of methods which make use of reflection in order to compare, hash, and stringify an objects public getters.
    Reflective.DataClass
    Extend this class if you do not want the Java default implementations of Object.equals(Object), Object.hashCode(), and Object.toString().
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Nullable
    Reminds anyone that this variable could intentionally have 'null' as a value, and that it should be checked before usage.
    PackagePrivate
    Indicates that the absence of a visibility modifier is intended to be package-private and was not simply forgotten.
    Reflective.Member
    If a getter is annotated with Reflective.Member, it will be taken into account by methods in Reflective.

Package de.hshl.obj.meta Description

Some classes meant to simplify the usage of the Java language in this project.

Contains annotations, such as Nullable and PackagePrivate. Also contains Reflective, which implements Object.toString(), Object.hashCode() and Object.equals(java.lang.Object) using dynamic runtime inspection of a given classes contents.
Author:
Johannes Vollmer
